# Placeholder for `secrets/tailscale-authkey.age`. Generate a one-shot
# pre-auth key in the Tailscale admin console (Settings → Keys →
# Generate auth key), tagged `tag:st0x-oracle-server`. Save just the
# key (no whitespace) as the plaintext, then:
#
#   nix eval --raw --file ../keys.nix roles.ssh \
#     --apply 'builtins.concatStringsSep "\n"' \
#     | rage -e -R /dev/stdin -o secrets/tailscale-authkey.age /tmp/tailscale-authkey
#
# NixOS's `services.tailscale` reads this at boot and joins the tailnet.
